Here's a simple JavaScript function that adds a new option to a select list using a template. However, please note that this function does not sanitize the input, so it can be used only for trusted inputs. For untrusted inputs, you should always sanitize them to prevent potential security issues, such as cross-site scripting (XSS).

```javascript
function addOptionToList(selectId, value, text) {
    // Get the select element by its ID
    var select = document.getElementById(selectId);

    // Create a new option element
    var option = document.createElement('option');

    // Set the value and text of the option
    option.value = value;
    option.text = text;

    // Append the option to the select element
    select.appendChild(option);
}
```

You can use this function like this:

```javascript
addOptionToList('mySelect', '1', 'Option 1');
```

This will add a new option with the value '1' and the text 'Option 1' to the select element with the ID 'mySelect'.

