This JavaScript function `searchAll` is triggered when the search input changes or when the search button is clicked. It first retrieves the search keyword from the input field. If a keyword is provided, it updates the browser's URL to include the search keyword using `window.history.pushState`. Then, it constructs a search URL and uses the `fetch` API to retrieve search results for members and entities. Upon successful retrieval, it displays the results in the respective sections of the page. Each member and entity result is displayed as a card with an image, name, and description.

