In this example, we have an input field where the user can enter a download link, and a button that triggers the download when clicked. The JavaScript function listens for the button click event, checks if the input field is not empty, and if so, creates a temporary anchor element with the href attribute set to the value of the input field. The download attribute is set to the filename extracted from the link. The anchor element is then appended to the body of the document, clicked to trigger the download, and removed from the document. If the input field is empty, an alert is displayed asking the user to enter a download link.

