<form method="post">
    <input type="text" name="data" placeholder="Enter data">
    <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>

<!-- login.html -->
<form method="post">
    <input type="text" name="username" placeholder="Enter username">
    <input type="password" name="password" placeholder="Enter password">
    <input type="submit" value="Login">
</form>
```

Please replace `'your_secret_key'` with a real secret key for your Flask application. Also, this example does not include secure storage of passwords. In a production environment, you should use a secure password hashing library like Werkzeug or Flask-Bcrypt.

