Here's a simple JavaScript function that initializes iframes for embedding content and adjusts their height based on postMessage events:

```javascript
function initIframes() {
    var iframes = document.querySelectorAll('iframe');

    iframes.forEach(function(iframe) {
        iframe.onload = function() {
            adjustIframeHeight(iframe);
        };

        iframe.addEventListener('message', function(event) {
            if (event.origin !== 'http://example.com') {
                return; // Only accept messages from a trusted origin
            }

            if (event.data === 'resize') {
                adjustIframeHeight(iframe);
            }
        });
    });
}

function adjustIframeHeight(iframe) {
    iframe.style.height = '0px'; // Reset height to 0 before measuring
    iframe.style.height = iframe.contentWindow.document.body.scrollHeight + 'px';
}
```

To use this function, simply call `initIframes()` when the page loads. The function will initialize all iframes on the page and set up event listeners for the `load` and `message` events.

The `adjustIframeHeight()` function is called when the iframe loads and when it receives a message with the data 'resize'. It sets the height of the iframe to the height of the content inside the iframe.

Note that the `event.origin` check is important to prevent cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. Only accept messages from a trusted origin (in this example, 'http://example.com'). You should replace 'http://example.com' with the actual origin of the content you are embedding.

